{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "A list of search terms was created by using the list of stressful life events and iteratively applying the whole script to the notes to avoid having a large number of false positives (for example, the terms \"married\" and \"divorced\" were excluded, because many notes contained marital status, e.g.",
    "\"Pt is married\", while we were looking for changes in marital status, such as \"recently married\").Only patients with notes containing these types of possible signal were selected for further processing.",
    "A pattern-matching R script can be found in the supplement A.We then created a few-shot learning LLM template for extracting stressful life events.",
    "from social histories in clinical notes with the Mixtral 8 × 7B model [34].",
    "This model provides high performance compared to similar-sized alternative models, according to independent benchmarks, such as Hugging Face, and this model quantized to 4 bits was the largest model that was feasible to run on-premises with existing resources in a secure computing environment (since we had sensitive data in the notes that contains Personally Identifiable Information, using cloud LLMs like OpenAI was not an option)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "from social histories in clinical notes with the Mixtral 8 × 7B model [34]."
  ]
}